   LLM         VLM      Agents   Retrieval   Tools

👉 CCL sits BETWEEN orchestration and execution.
It does not decide what to do — it ensures everything can work together cleanly.

⸻

2. Core Responsibilities

2.1 Semantic Translation

Convert all subsystem outputs → shared schema

y_i \rightarrow \tilde{y}_i

⸻

2.2 State Synchronization

Ensure all modules operate on consistent context
	•	shared session state
	•	partial outputs become priors
	•	no drift between subsystems

⸻

2.3 Message Passing

Acts as a publish/subscribe bus
	•	modules don’t talk directly
	•	everything flows through CCL

⸻

2.4 Conflict Mediation

When outputs disagree:
	•	detect contradiction
	•	escalate to:
	•	Mirror (constraints)
	•	Hound (anomaly detection)
	•	Checksum (truth/provenance)

⸻

2.5 Provenance + Confidence Preservation

Every piece of data carries:
	•	source
	•	transformation history
	•	confidence score

⸻

2.6 Compositional Enablement

Allows chaining:

VLM → CCL → LLM → CCL → Agent → CCL → Output


